-- Maryland Pushes to Require 2% Solar Power by 2020
-- B y   E h r e n   G o o s s e n s
-- 2012-05-22T18:40:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-22/maryland-pushes-to-require-2-solar-power-by-2020.html
Maryland moved forward the date by
which utilities must get 2 percent of their electricity from
solar power by two years to 2020.  Maryland Governor Martin O’Malley, a Democrat, signed a
bill changing the target today, according to his website.  The law was passed by the state’s legislature April 6.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ehren Goossens in  New York  at 
